The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, December 13, 2003  Fond Fantasy for 2000 Guineas 
 FROM WILLIAM TELL		 GanapathyBangalore: Son Of The Light and Fond Fantasy look the best of the six runners to fight it out for the 1,600m Harvins Bangalore 2000 Guineas, the second classic of the season and main attraction here on Saturday.				 										Both are classic winners in Maysore and are in the pink of condition, too. But in Mysore, Fond Fantasy, despite her 4 kg weight disadvantage, had handed an easy beating to Son Of The Light. Therefore, the former, a S. Ganapathy-ward and with B. Prakash to guide, may win on the Razeen-Excentrique filly.				 										SELECTIONS				 										1.30 pm: Brilliant Diamond 1. Royal Ribbons 2. Touch Of Frost 3.				 										2 pm: Samarinda 1. Flying Fortune 2. Shakalaka Baby 3.				 										2.30 pm: Spectacular Quest 1. Vishnupriya 2. Flightingale 3.				 										3 pm: Almond 1. Southern Goddess 2. Marmalade 3.				 										3.30 pm: Generic Emperor 1. Kings Pride 2. Saladin 3.				 										4 pm: Fond Fantasy 1. Son Of The Light 2. Lancaster 3.				 										4.30 pm: Poem 1. Pelf 2. Ithica 3.				 										5 pm: Accordance 1. Rubik 2. Silent Memory 3.				 										Days Best: Fond Fantasy Double: Samarinda amp; Generic Emperor
